LBMA-Statistics

Web data extraction from Statistics of the London Bullion Market (London Gold Fixing, London Silver Fixing).

See http://www.lbma.org.uk/pages/index.cfm?page_id=48 for details on London Bullion Market and available Statistics.

Information returned by this module is governed by LBMA's terms and conditions.

"If you wish to use the gold or silver Fixing prices for commercial purposes,
 including to incorporate them into commercial products which you intend to market,
 sell or otherwise provide to third parties, you must pay the required fee and obtain
 a licence from The London Gold Market Fixing Limited and / or The London Silver Market
 Fixing Limited as appropriate. See www.goldfixing.com and www.silverfixing.com for full details."

http://www.lbma.org.uk/pages/?page_id=53&title=gold_fixings


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

EXTENDED NETWORK TESTS

To enable extended tests set the NETWORK_TEST enviroment variable
e.g. 
    $ NETWORK_TEST=1 make test
or
    $ NETWORK_TEST=1 prove -l -v t/*

These tests require a working internet connection.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc LBMA::Statistics

Have a look at the examples directory, too.

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=LBMA-Statistics

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/LBMA-Statistics

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/LBMA-Statistics

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/LBMA-Statistics/


